Biography: I am a Full Professor at Paris-Saclay University, Director of the International Laboratory on Learning Systems (ILLS) and affiliate with the National Centre for Scientific Research (CNRS). I am also a Associate Academic Member at Mila - Quebec AI Institute and Associate Professor at ETS Montreal. My research lies at the intersection of security, privacy, and machine learning, and the broader applications to various domains such as healthcare, security and automation. I am especially interested in collaborative agents-AI systems designed to interact, negotiate, and cooperate with both humans and other machines to achieve shared goals. My work aims to develop rigorous, information-theoretic techniques for building safe, trustworthy, and robust multi-agent AI systems, thereby fostering confidence in their behavior and enabling their reliable deployment in societal contexts. Previously, my research had a broader interest in Information Theory-the mathematical framework for understanding and quantifying information and its applications to numerous areas of applied mathematics and science such as fundamental limits of distributed compression, statistical decision theory, universal source coding, cooperation, feedback, index coding, and security of communication channels. I served as Program General Chair of the 2019 IEEE International Symposium on Information Theory (ISIT), and Area Chair and Senior Area Chair in several conferences such AAAI, ISIT, ITW, CCS, USENIX, NeurIPS, among others, and as Associate Editor for the IEEE Trans. on Information Forensics and Security. I earned my Ph.D. in Physics from Universite Paris-Sud (France) in 2007. Upon graduating, I joined the Department of Telecommunications at Supelec and in 2015 the Laboratoire des Signaux et Systemes (L2S) within Paris-Saclay University. From 2018 to 2019, I was visiting professor at University of Montreal (Canada) and ETS Montreal and from 2019 to 2020, I was visiting researcher at Laboratoire de Mathematiques dOrsay (France). Previusly, I was visiting professor at University of Chile (Chile), University of Buenos Aires (Argentina), TU Wien - Technische Universitat Wien (Austria), Technion (Israel), EPFL - Ecole Polytechnique Federale de Lausanne (Switzerland).

Biography: Luc Tremblay : Stratege | Innovateur | Facilitateur Fort d'une carriere distinguee de quarante ans, Luc Tremblay s'est impose comme une force redoutable dans la croissance strategique des affaires et l'innovation. Son parcours au sein des leaders technologiques mondiaux et ses entreprises entrepreneuriales ont forge une expertise unique et multifacette, parfaitement adaptee pour guider les organisations a travers des transformations complexes et des expansions de marche. Luc maitrise le processus de mise sur le marche, de la conception a l'execution, livrant constamment des revenus accrus et une part de marche etendue. Une carriere forgee dans la croissance et l'innovation La vaste experience de Luc temoigne de son adaptabilite et de son esprit avant-gardiste. Il a occupe des roles pivots dans un large eventail de fonctions commerciales, notamment la Strategie, la Gestion, les Operations, les Ventes, le Developpement des affaires et le Marketing. Cette comprehension holistique du paysage commercial lui permet de concevoir et de mettre en oeuvre des strategies qui sont non seulement visionnaires mais aussi operationnellement solides. Sa carriere est marquee par un theme constant : la conduite du nouveau . Chez /N SPRO, en tant que VP Marketing et Developpement des affaires, il a ete l'architecte du lancement de nouvelles offres de produits et de l'etablissement d'une presence dans de nouvelles zones geographiques. Au cours de son mandat chez Nakisa, il a joue un role determinant dans le lancement de leur Programme de partenariat mondial et a mene avec succes l'entree de l'entreprise sur le marche latino-americain. Peut-etre l'une des experiences les plus revelatrices a ete son passage chez SAP, ou il a ete un membre fondateur de l'equipe qui a lance les plateformes revolutionnaires SAP NetWeaver et SAP xApps. Ce role exigeait non seulement une comprehension technique approfondie, mais aussi le sens strategique pour eduquer le marche, batir un pipeline de ventes a partir de zero et etablir un modele de revenus durable pour des solutions entierement nouvelles. Methodologies eprouvees pour un succes previsible Luc ne se fie pas uniquement a son intuition. Il est un praticien certifie de cadres de strategie commerciale de renommee mondiale, y compris la Strategie Ocean Bleu et les methodologies Strategyzer pour la construction d'entreprises invincibles et le test d'idees commerciales. Cet engagement envers des approches eprouvees et axees sur les donnees garantit que ses conseils sont ancres dans les meilleures pratiques qui attenuent les risques et maximisent les chances de succes. Sa recente certification en Building Invincible Companies de Strategyzer en mai 2024 souligne son devouement a l'apprentissage continu et a rester a la pointe de l'innovation strategique. Leadership et perspective globale Les capacites de leadership de Luc s'etendent au-dela des roles d'entreprise. Ses 12 annees de service au conseil d'administration de Desjardins, y compris un mandat en tant que President, demontrent sa competence en matiere de gouvernance, de surveillance strategique et de leadership ethique au sein d'une cooperative financiere majeure. De plus, son experience en tant que Chef de l'exploitation mondial pour le Groupe AUTHENTIC et son travail dans l'etablissement d'operations nord-americaines pour une entreprise basee au Bresil lui ont fourni des informations inestimables sur les nuances culturelles des affaires internationales, en particulier entre l'Amerique du Nord, l'Amerique latine et l'Europe. Le partenaire ideal pour votre mandat Aujourd'hui, en tant que PDG de Tremblay Strategie Innovation, Luc consacre son temps a aider les entreprises en tant que consultant, coach et facilitateur. Il apporte une combinaison rare d'experience pratique, de prevoyance strategique et d'une boite a outils de methodologies eprouvees. Pour toute organisation cherchant a naviguer dans les complexites d'un nouveau marche, a lancer un nouveau produit ou a transformer fondamentalement sa direction strategique, Luc Tremblay n'offre pas seulement des conseils, mais un partenariat. Ses 40 ans de succes sont l'assurance ultime qu'il possede l'expertise, le savoir-faire et les connaissances necessaires pour faciliter votre mandat et propulser votre organisation vers un avenir plus rentable et innovant.

Biography: Lucas Russell is the founder and CEO of Goverly.ai, the Canadian startup that decided government procurement didnt have to be a maze designed by Kafka and managed by Excel. Goverly is building an AI-powered platform that helps businesses instantly understand RFPs, grants, and contract opportunities, then match with the right government program-provincial, territorial, or federal. In short: Goverly turns bureaucratic headache into business opportunity. With Goverly Defence, Lucas is tackling one of Canadas most complex puzzles: Industrial and Technological Benefits (ITBs). Instead of forcing prime contractors and SMEs to slog through endless paperwork, Goverly Defence automates the matchmaking and compliance, helping both sides meet obligations faster, cheaper, and with fewer grey hairs. Before Goverly, Lucas built and exited ventures in fintech, health tech, and AI services, each time refining his knack for turning impossible processes into usable products. His past work taught him how to navigate regulatory hurdles, translate technical complexity into plain English, and-most importantly-spot when a system is so broken its begging to be rebuilt. Goverly is the culmination of that pattern: a platform born from years of staring at government contracts and asking, why does it have to be this hard? Lucas has pitched on international stages, worked alongside provincial and federal governments, and convinced investors, bureaucrats, and skeptics alike that AI can actually make government easier to work with. Hes known for his ability to blend sharp strategy with humor-because nothing makes procurement reform more palatable than a well-timed joke about compliance checklists. Outside of Goverly, Lucas is a Canadian entrepreneur who has coached novice soccer teams, tested more startup ideas than most people test coffee blends, and built a reputation for asking why not? at the exact moment others are listing reasons why not. His approach to entrepreneurship is equal parts fearless, practical, and mischievous. At this conference, Lucas isnt just here to talk about Goverly (though he will happily demo how AI can chew through a hundred-page RFP in seconds). Hes here to connect with fellow builders, researchers, and policy thinkers who share his obsession with taking AI out of the lab and into the messiest, most consequential corners of the real world. If you want to discuss AI for procurement, sovereign tech, defence, or government innovation, Lucas will have ideas. If you want to talk soccer strategy, Canadian small-cap markets, or the best way to pitch a room full of skeptics, hell have stories. And if you just want to laugh about the absurdity of government paperwork while secretly believing it can be fixed-hes definitely your guy. Disclaimer: conversations with Lucas may result in new startup ideas, unexpected collaborations, or sudden optimism about government actually working better.

L'infrastructure IA de notre pays est a la fois diversifiee et solide, ancree dans des institutions de classe mondiale telles que Mila, Vector Institute, et Amii, ainsi que dans des etablissements educatifs renommes comme Smith's a l'Universite Queen's et de nombreux autres piliers academiques a travers le pays. Cette synergie collaborative, reliant l'academie, le gouvernement et le secteur public, cree un environnement propice a l'investissement, favorisant l'innovation et stimulant une croissance durable. A la communaute des multinationales internationales: les secteurs de l'IA et des Services Financiers du Canada regorgent de potentiel inexploite. Se connecter avec moi est votre passerelle pour naviguer et capitaliser sur ces opportunites, en alignant vos ambitions d'investissement et les objectifs de votre entreprise avec les atouts inegales du Canada. Si le Canada figure sur votre radar d'investissement, je vous invite chaleureusement a me contacter. Ensemble, nous pourrons faconner et realiser votre vision, garantissant un succes sans precedent dans le paysage evolutif de l'IA.

Biography: David Kershaw Founder, No-Code Engineering nocodeengineering.io David Kershaw is the founder of No-Code Engineering, a company focused on governing automation systems at scale. For nearly a decade he has worked as a high-autonomy contractor in enterprise environments, stabilizing fragile automations and introducing governance frameworks where they were missing. His specialization is no-code and low-code orchestration - platforms such as Workfront Fusion and Make.com - where automation estates expand quickly but oversight often lags. Davids approach centers on blueprint-native interrogation and automated design governance. Instead of waiting for failures in production, he works at the design layer to surface risks around complexity, environment separation, pagination, and scalability before they reach the business. This philosophy underpins his current product development: tools that make automation flows more legible, interrogable, and governable. By focusing on design-time governance, these tools give organizations visibility into risks that would otherwise remain hidden inside sprawling automation footprints. In parallel, David publishes essays and system notes at nocodeengineering.io, where he writes about automation governance, scale challenges, and enterprise system clarity. His emphasis is on substance over optics - building automation systems that reflect how businesses actually work, not just how they appear on dashboards. David has been invited to speak at ecosystem events, contribute to AI and automation conferences, and participate in accelerator programs aimed at formalizing governance tooling for the next wave of enterprise automation. Based in Fredericton, New Brunswick, David balances his professional work with family life and ongoing exploration of system design at scale.

Biography: Pamela Snively is the Chief Data & Trust Officer at TELUS. She leads the team responsible for privacy governance and data ethics, along with data management and a number of compliance functions, including the Anti-bribery & Corruption and Competition Law programs. Pam approaches overall data governance through the lens of customer trust, leveraging TELUS CustomerFirst principle to drive the organizations commitment to privacy and data ethics.Pam is a lawyer but has dedicated most of her career to developing and operationalizing privacy best practices, either as a consultant or in-house. Under Pams leadership, TELUS has significantly transformed its approach to transparency about its data handling practices. This has included a refresh of the TELUS Privacy Centre to include layered information on TELUS' datamanagement practices, as well as some best practices to help our customers protect their information. Pam has also published the framework for her privacy management program online, encouraging TELUS customers to more fully understand what responsible private sector organizations do to protect privacy.Pamela was the recipient of the 2017 Ontario Bar Associations Karen Spector Memorial Award for Excellence in Privacy Law. She participates in a number of national and international think-tanks and governance bodies related to privacy and data governance, including serving as a Board member for the Information Accountability Foundation and on the Privacy and Data Advisory Committee for the Canadian Marketing Association. She is also a founding member and Chair of Canadas Business Privacy Group, a working group made up of some of Canadas leading privacy professionals and industry associations focused on building trust in Canadas digital ecosystem and legislative regime.Pam is a frequent speaker on privacy and data ethics and she actively encourages other organizations to join her in her mission to earn and elevate consumer trust in our digital ecosystem.

Biography: Working as a Dental Surgeon and clinic owner by day, and a PhD candidate in A.I. at Universite Paris Cite by night. I operate at the convergence of clinical practice and deep learning. My research explores the potential of repurposing routine dental radiographs for opportunistic health screening. By developing advanced A.I. models, I aim to extract biomarkers for systemic conditions, such as osteoporosis, from this commonly available imaging data. The ultimate objective is to establish a low-cost, scalable method for early disease detection that integrates seamlessly into existing healthcare workflows. Firmly believing that research must lead to tangible solutions, I am also an entrepreneur in the health-tech space. I focus on building businesses that can take promising AI models, like the ones in my research, from the lab to the clinic, ensuring they deliver real value to doctors and patients. l am here at ALL IN to connect with fellow innovators passionate about building clinically-relevant A.I. solutions. If you're interested in medical imaging, predictive analytics, or shaping the future of diagnostics, I would love to start a conversation.

Biography: Brett is a recognized innovation leadership expert. As an organizational psychologist, consultant and researcher, he adds a unique psychodynamic perspective to manage the tricky aspects of innovation and change. He serves as a trustworthy thought partner to senior executives in central banks, leading corporates, tier 1 consultancies and high-growth startups. Originally trained as an economist while also an athlete and then coach in Canadas Olympic development system, his approach has always been grounded in business realities and the psychology of high performance. As recognized by over 200 awards and patents when he served as an innovation leader living in Vancouver, Paris and London-working with innovators like Apple, Google, Jaguar Land Rover, AMEX, Barclays, Diageo and Unilever. In 2019, he sharpened his leadership development practice at INSEAD-the leading global business school based in Fontainebleau, France. During the three-year Executive Master of Change (systems psychodynamics), Brett focused his research on the psychology of effective innovation leadership-receiving distinction in 2021. A product of this research, The Innovation Leadership Map (ILM) has become a powerful leadership development tool to help professionals more effectively achieve higher impact, healthier teams and happier careers. Brett has a specialist interest in treating impulse control, burnout and loss of confidence from workplace challenges such as excessive expectations or permanent frustration. Symptoms that are often addressed by ILM and clinical leadership development programs for more positive professional and personal outcomes. Outside his private practice, Brett advises the G20 Leaders Summit on digital leaders, is an advisory-backed investor with Working Title Capital and is a board advisor. Socially, he cycles as an official Rapha Cycle Club, enjoys alpine pursuits and loves good food. Vancouver based, globally active!

Over a span of 25 years in the visual effects (VFX) industry, I've had the privilege of contributing to many memorable movies and TV shows, leveraging my background in fine arts, business, and industrial engineering to lead teams at top North American VFX studios. This journey instilled a profound understanding of storytelling through visuals, a skill I've come to realize has much in common with another passion of mine: simplifying complex business decisions. The leap from VFX to tech entrepreneurship might seem wide, but the thread connecting them is visual storytelling. In VFX, we use visuals to make complex narratives understandable and engaging. I saw an opportunity to apply this approach to the often rigid and inaccessible world of financial modeling. Traditional business planning tools, dominated by spreadsheets, lacked the flexibility and intuitiveness that a more visual approach could offer. This realization sparked the idea for whatifi. Management struggles with countless high-stakes decisions. Cash flow. Capacity planning. SaaS pricing. Fundraising. Debt. M&A. Growth. Churn. whatifi is born from a desire to revolutionize how businesses approach financial modeling and strategic planning. Our ecosystem helps decision-makers to create visual "what if" scenarios, making it easier to understand the potential outcomes of different business decisions. It's designed to be intuitive, leveraging a decision-tree methodology that visually maps out complex decision paths and outcomes. This approach not only makes financial planning more accessible but also fosters collaboration and creativity among team members. As the founder of whatifi, my goal is to bridge the gap between the dynamic, visual logic of VFX and the strategic needs of business planning. We've built whatifi to help entrepreneurs and business leaders visualize the impact of their decisions in a way that's as engaging and informative as a well-crafted story. It's a tool that reflects my journey from creating compelling visuals on screen to enabling businesses to paint their futures with broader, more informed strokes. In pitching whatifi, I'm not just introducing a new product; I'm advocating for a shift in how we approach business planning and decision-making. It's a journey from the creative confines of VFX studios to the entrepreneurial challenge of redefining an industry. And it's just beginning.

Biography: Im an immigration lawyer who decided the old way of doing things wasnt good enough. After a decade in legal practice-spanning Common Law (J.D.) and Civil Law (LL.B.), managing firms, litigating, and closing over $1M in immigration service sales-I hit the same wall every immigration professional knows: outdated tools, manual workflows, and a model that scales costs instead of results. Rather than hire more staff to patch the problem, I built a new model. Enter Immigratio-a proprietary, AI-driven case management platform designed to automate up to 85% of immigration workflows for lawyers and licensed consultants. Born out of my own firms pain points, Immigratio isnt just software-its a re-engineering of how immigration cases are prepared, filed, and managed across Canadian and U.S. jurisdictions. As NAIAs co-founder and head of product vision, I fuse my deep legal expertise with a relentless focus on real-world application. My dual training and hands-on experience managing both Common Law and Civil Law cases mean Immigratio is built to work seamlessly in multiple legal systems. The platforms AI automates document collection, form completion, and compliance checks, while giving lawyers more time to focus on high-value strategy instead of clerical grind. In under two years, weve gone from concept to active beta with 10 law firms and consultants-over 200 real cases processed through the platform. The impact? Measurable time savings, lower error rates, and an entirely new way to scale legal practice without scaling overhead. Im not here to replace lawyers. Im here to make them radically more effective-turning AI into an everyday ally for legal professionals. At ALL IN 2025, Im sharing how we took a traditional, paper-heavy legal process and rebuilt it into an AI-powered, future-proof workflow-one thats already transforming immigration law practice. _------------------------------------------------ Je suis avocat specialise en droit de l'immigration et j'ai decide que l'ancienne facon de faire ne suffisait plus. Apres une decennie de pratique juridique, couvrant la common law (J.D.) et le droit civil (LL.B.), la gestion de cabinets, le contentieux et la cloture de plus d'un million de dollars de ventes de services d'immigration, je me suis heurte au meme obstacle que tout professionnel de l'immigration : des outils obsoletes, des flux de travail manuels et un modele qui ajuste les couts au detriment des resultats. Plutot que d'embaucher du personnel pour resoudre le probleme, j'ai cree un nouveau modele. Voici Immigratio, une plateforme exclusive de gestion de dossiers basee sur l'IA, concue pour automatiser jusqu'a 85 % des flux de travail en matiere d'immigration pour les avocats et les consultants agrees. Nee des difficultes rencontrees par mon propre cabinet, Immigratio n'est pas qu'un simple logiciel : c'est une refonte de la preparation, du depot et de la gestion des dossiers d'immigration au Canada et aux Etats-Unis. En tant que cofondateur et responsable de la vision produit de NAIA, je combine ma solide expertise juridique a une attention constante portee a l'application concrete. Ma double formation et mon experience pratique de la gestion de dossiers de common law et de droit civil permettent a Immigratio de fonctionner de maniere transparente dans de nombreux systemes juridiques. L'IA de la plateforme automatise la collecte de documents, le remplissage des formulaires et les controles de conformite, tout en laissant aux avocats plus de temps pour se concentrer sur des strategies a forte valeur ajoutee plutot que sur des taches administratives fastidieuses. En moins de deux ans, nous sommes passes du concept a la version beta active avec 10 cabinets d'avocats et consultants ; plus de 200 dossiers reels ont ete traites via la plateforme. L'impact ? Des gains de temps mesurables, une reduction des taux d'erreur et une toute nouvelle facon de developper la pratique juridique sans augmenter les frais generaux. Je ne suis pas la pour remplacer les avocats. Je suis la pour les rendre radicalement plus efficaces, en faisant de l'IA un allie au quotidien des professionnels du droit. Lors de la conference ALL IN 2025, je partage comment nous avons transforme un processus juridique traditionnel, lourd en papier, en un flux de travail perenne et optimise par l'IA, qui transforme deja la pratique du droit de l'immigration.

Biography: My passion for building MemreeAI started in 2024 with a burning desire to use my knowledge and skills to make a difference in people's lives. So I dropped out of my PhD program after one year because I didn't see my research making an impact on anyone's lives, and I founded Memree. Since then, it's been an arduous journey full of heartbreaks, rejections, sleepless nights, panic, stress, and some good news here and there. But will I choose any other life than this? HELL NO. I have lived the first 30 years of my life building things for others and living a mundane yet comfortable life. And through the first 30 years of my lived experience, I realised that, that life is not for me. I always knew that I wanted to be an entrepreneur. I knew I had the risk appetite, the hunger for building something greater than me, the hunger for excellence, and the passion to build things that help others. I just didn't have the courage to make the move earlier. I needed a "point-of-no-return". That came in the form of getting fired from a job, massive credit card debt, and severe anxiety. I knew this was my calling to make a move. And now, despite all the hardships, I know why I chose this life. Because I am meant to be an entrepreneur. This is who I am. I don't seek comfort, I don't seek safety. All I want is to make a company that will outlast me, will feed hundreds (if not thousands) of families who work for the company. I would consider that a life well lived. Being part of the NEXT AI was one of our biggest achievements. And now being able to present our passion in front of thousands of people in the ALL IN event is magical. In this journey, I also found my co-founder, Karen Southwell, who keeps me in check and keeps our company moving in the right direction. Without her, Memree and I would both be lost.

Biography: Guillaume est co-fondateur, chef de la direction et president du Conseil d'administration de FX Innovation, une entreprise specialisee dans la transformation numerique, et positionnee parmi les plus importantes PME quebecoises et canadiennes. Entrepreneur visionnaire et passionne, il s'interesse particulierement a la comprehension du cycle d'adoption des nouvelles technologies dans les differentes industries et deploie son energie a developper avec ses equipes une vision claire, mobilisante et ambitieuse pour son organisation. D'autres part, il est important pour Guillaume de prendre part a l'ecosysteme entrepreneurial ainsi qu'a celui de l'innovation quebecois et canadien, notamment par son implication au sein du Canadian Council of Innovators ainsi qu'au Centre de Recherche Informatique de Montreal (CRIM) a titre de president du Conseil d'administration. Guillaume is co-founder, CEO and Chairman of the Board of FX Innovation, a company specialized in digital transformation and positioned among the most important SMEs in Quebec and Canada. A visionary and passionate entrepreneur, he is particularly interested in understanding the adoption cycle of new technologies in different industries and deploys his energy to develop with his teams a clear, mobilizing and ambitious vision for his organization. It is also important for Guillaume to take part in the entrepreneurial ecosystem as well as in the Quebec and Canadian innovation ecosystem, notably through his involvement with the Canadian Council of Innovators and the Centre de Recherche Informatique de Montreal (CRIM) as Chairman of the Board.

Cest dans cette attitude de depassement constante quil progresse et chemine pour sa propre entreprise mais aussi, et toujours, pour ses clients actuels et futurs! Biography: I founded Foci Solutions to help software companies build better and faster engineering teams. I am passionate about instilling a culture of learning and curiosity in teams and believe that is the key to unlocking future potential. I believe that the strongest companies are those who optimize for future potential rather than point-in-time productivity. I am a technology realist that believes in the potential and power of AI, but also recognize the need to adopt it responsibly and sustainably. I love working on real-world enterprise scale applications of AI beyond just chatbots and co-pilots. At Foci Solutions, we help large enterprise and public sector clients automate and transform their most critical business processes and services through the adoption of modern technology such as Cloud and AI. We have worked with customers all over the globe and across a broad range of sectors ranging from biotechnology to cybersecurity. But we don't just build apps or technology solutions. We also help our clients build teams and capacity. We believe that technology is only valuable is our clients can sustain them without us. We partner with our clients to ensure they have the necessary skills and resources to continue to sustain and evolve our solutions long after the project is done.

Biography: Dr. Ahmed Ragab is a Lead Scientist in AI at Natural Resources Canada (NRCan). He is also an Adjunct Professor at the Department of Mathematics and Industrial Engineering, Polytechnique Montreal. He received a Ph.D. degree in Industrial Engineering from Polytechnique Montreal, the University of Montreal, Canada in 2014. Dr. Ragabs research interests include AI, Machine Learning, Pattern Recognition, Image Processing, Data & Decisions Fusion, Causality Analysis, Reliability Modeling, Operations Research, Discrete Event Systems, and Process Mining. His main thematic activities focus on the practical challenges of Big Data and AI in several industrial applications including Abnormal Events Diagnosis & Prognosis, Predictive Maintenance, Supervisory Control, Real-time Optimization, Production Scheduling, and Systems Design. Dr. Ragab has a bunch of experience in developing advanced AI algorithms and tools in the manufacturing industry, aiming at reducing energy consumption, Greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions, and operational and maintenance costs while improving operations performance. He also teaches industrial engineering courses at graduate levels and supervises MSc and PhD students.

Biography: Im a serial entrepreneur based in Canada. My goal : create wealth for my community and work for a sustainable and socially responsible world. I joined CONFORMiT in September 2015 as owner, President & Chief Executive Officer. CONFORMiT is a leading global Environmental, Health & Safety Management (EHS) SaaS solution. With clients in 20 countries with more than 700,000 users, CONFORMiT is one of the international leaders that offers a complete set of solutions to help organizations better manage their EHS processes - in the simplest way. From 2010 to August 2015, I was in charge of the development (Sales & Delivery) in Central of Europe and Nordic countries with PCO Innovation (now Accenture). In 2002, I founded a company that offers strategic consulting services in information technology. Under my leadership, the company experienced strong growth and became a key player in the Canadian market. I launched five other successful companies in the fields of technology, internet services, consulting and food service. I also held the position of vice-president of outsourcing and telecommunication at Cognicase, a company with $400 million in sales, Cognicase was acquired by CGI in 2003. I was in the Canadian Armed Forces for seven years.

Biography: Engineer, passionate about innovation and intellectual property (IP) strategy. My work has been focused on intellectual property for nearly 30 years. I am passionate about innovation and about supporting clients on IP matters throughout their journey. I am familiar with all aspects of patent procurement in Canada and the United States, including: preparing and prosecuting applications; managing IP portfolios; conducting freedom-to-operate assessments; and developing strategies that support the business objectives of clients. I provide counselling and support during IP due diligence during transactions. I also work with litigation teams by offering expertise in the preparation of patent infringement and validity opinions. My particular technical expertise lies in the areas of electronics, telecommunications, business methods, control systems, medical devices, machine learning, Artificial Intelligence, software and related technologies. I am passionate about about increasing awareness of the strategic importance of intellectual property rights in the local business community and in particular for small and medium sized companies (SMEs).

Job Title: Associe, avocat, Co-Leader, Technologies et intelligence artificielle
Attendee Category: Service Provider - Other professional services

Biography: Julien specializes in advising companies on intellectual property matters relating to software, with a particular interest in artificial intelligence and other emerging technologies. He is a professional engineer who completed is Master of Advanced Studies in data mining at GERAD, a multi university research center regrouping experts from HEC Montreal, Polytechnique Montreal, McGill University and Universite du Quebec a Montreal. He is also a registered patent agent in Canada and the United States. Julien has extensive experience in the building of patent portfolios for companies of various sizes, from start-up ventures looking to increase their value and attract funding, to multinational organizations preparing to enter new markets. Julien has particular experience drafting and prosecuting patent applications in the United States, Canada, Europe and China, advising on patent infringement and avoidance issues, and shaping and implementing comprehensive intellectual property strategies supporting business objectives and corporate strategies. Julien is a member of the Organizing Committee of Le Forum international de la propriete intellectuelle - Quebec (FORPIQ), a non-profit organization devoted to increasing the level of knowledge of innovative Canadian companies and their advisers about intellectual property assets. Julien also guest-lectures on design patents and animates a workshop on patent filing strategy and a workshop on advanced claim drafting for the IPIC program at McGill University.
